[[Image:Frühlingslandschft Aaretal Schweiz.jpg|thumb|right|Agricultural road in Switzerland]] An '''agricultural road''' or '''farm track''' is a [[service road]] that serves predominantly [[agriculture|agricultural]] or [[forestry]] purposes and has only local significance. Agricultural roads are typically unpaved [[dirt road]]s or covered with [[gravel]], but in some cases [[asphalt]] roads are agricultural roads.<ref>{{Citation |publisher = Thomas D. Larson Pennsylvania Transportation Institute |last = Scheetz |first = Barry E |author2 = Steven M Bloser |title = Environmentally Sensitive Maintenance on Agricultural Roads to Reduce Nutrient and Sediment Pollution in the Kishacoquillas Watershed |accessdate = 2014-05-17 |date = 2009-12-31 |url = http://www.dirtandgravel.psu.edu/Research/Documents/CIG_web.pdf |archive-url = https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20130825154132/http://www.dirtandgravel.psu.edu/research/documents/CIG_web.pdf |dead-url = yes |archive-date = 2013-08-25 |df = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | volume = 50 | issue = 2 | last = Tolliver | first = Denver | title = Modeling Investments in County and Local Roads to Support Agricultural Logistics | journal = Journal of the Transportation Research Forum | accessdate = 2014-05-17 | date = 2011 | url = http://www.trforum.org/journal/downloads/2011v50n2_07_ModelingInvestments.pdf }}</ref>
In the [[United States]], a "[[farm-to-market road]]" or "ranch-to-market road" (sometimes "farm road" or "ranch road" for short) is a [[state road]] or [[county road]] that connects [[rural]] or [[agricultural]] areas to market towns.<ref name="FM facts">{{cite web |publisher=Texas Department of Transportation |author=Staff |url=http://www.dot.state.tx.us/tpp/hwy/fmfacts.htm|title=Farm/Ranch to Market Facts |accessdate=February 26, 2008 }}</ref><ref name="UR Chron">{{cite news |last=Babineck |first= Mark |title=Tex-Arcana: What's a farm-to-market road?|url=http://www.chron.com/disp/story.mpl/metropolitan/5065822.html |newspaper=Houston Chronicle |date=August 18, 2007 |accessdate=April 8, 2011}}</ref>
