'''Area code 441''' is the [[telephone]] [[area code]] for [[Bermuda]]. It was created by a split from the original [[area code 809]] on October 1, 1995, although permissive dialing continued until September 30, 1996.<ref>[https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=JyxYAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22area+code%22+441+1996&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Bermuda ''Toll-free Phone Book USA: A Directory of Toll-free Telephone Numbers for Business and Organizations Nationwide''], Kay Gill, Omnigraphics, 1997, page ix</ref> When calling from countries and territories outside the [[North American Numbering Plan]], the area code is prefixed by the [[international access code]] and the [[country calling code|country code]] '''1'''; for example from the [[United Kingdom]], subscribers would dial '''00 1 441'''.<ref>[https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=c28nAQAAIAAJ&q=Bermuda+%2200+1+441%22&dq=Bermuda+%2200+1+441%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjflNa296rMAhXJfhoKHRySAWIQ6AEIKzAA ''Maritime Guide''], The Register, 2001, page 68</ref>
From 1995 to 1999, each of the groups of the various Caribbean and Atlantic islands using the [[North American Numbering Plan]] area codes, which had previously shared [[area code 809]], was split off and given its own area code. 441 is among them. The 809 Area Code now exclusively serves the [[Dominican Republic]].
