'''Johann Jacob Heber''' (1666–1727) was a [[surveying|surveyor]] and [[geometrician]] from the city of [[Lindau]], Germany. He is the artist of the first map of the [[Liechtenstein|Principality of Liechtenstein]] on record, which he drew in 1721.<ref>[http://www.danstopicals.com/heber.htm Johann Jacob Heber]</ref>

Heber was the son of Jacob Heber and Elisabetha Catharina. He married Elisabetha Barbara Hartenstein, daughter of Philipp Mathias Hartenstein and Eva Katharina Spacke, on 26 January 1797 at Thaleischweiler, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany.<ref>[http://home.comcast.net/~rcgrein/Hartenstein/p11.htm]</ref>
