'''Kašina''' ({{IPA-sh|kâʃina|hr}}) is a settlement in the [[City of Zagreb]], [[Croatia]], population 1,548 (2011 census).<ref>{{Croatian Census 2011|S|21}}</ref> It is located around 22&nbsp;km north-east of the city centre of [[Zagreb]] and north of the district [[Sesvete]].

The first mention of Kašina is dated to 1217 in the charter of [[Andrew II of Hungary|King Andrew II]]. The church in Kašina was badly damaged in the [[1880 Zagreb earthquake]].

