'''Kuvan''' or '''Kuvan Darya''' is a dry riverbed of what once was a tributary of the [[Syr Darya|Syr]] river in Central Asia.<ref name=arch>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DguGWP0vGY8C&pg=PA467&lpg=PA467&dq=kuvan+darya&source=bl&ots=y2-3j_7ksX&sig=KzLWJSy6AqbewySEwyCXXWX4UT8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVwK-XuYrZAhVMAqwKHSKDDzUQ6AEISDAM#v=onepage&q=kuvan+darya&f=false|title=History of Civilizations of Central Asia: The development of sedentary and nomadic civilizations: 700 B.C. to A.D. 250|first=Ahmad Hasan|last=Dani|date=3 February 1999|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass Publ.|via=Google Books}}</ref> The area is located west of [[Kzyl-Orda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gdUUAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA85&lpg=PA85&dq=kuvan+darya&source=bl&ots=jWhrbA0pg2&sig=L_tJaVEHdFKMcMgwbc84Rp2m0hM&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVwK-XuYrZAhVMAqwKHSKDDzUQ6AEIPTAI#v=onepage&q=kuvan+darya&f=false|title=Archaeology in Soviet Central Asia|first=Grégoire|last=Frumkin|date=3 February 1970|publisher=Brill Archive|via=Google Books}}</ref> It is an area of archaeological interest and was once home to tigers whose range extensed to the reedy shores of the [[Aral Sea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UxWZ-OmTqVoC&pg=PA118&lpg=PA118&dq=kuvan+darya&source=bl&ots=RFkYHn5xt4&sig=Kr_7k8wrbkL6ED4tthisvXj7hBs&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVwK-XuYrZAhVMAqwKHSKDDzUQ6AEIQzAK#v=onepage&q=kuvan+darya&f=false|title=Mammals of the Soviet Union, Volume 2 Part 2 Carnivora (Hyenas and Cats)|first=V. G.|last=Heptner|date=3 February 1989|publisher=BRILL|via=Google Books}}</ref> The area includes unusual [[kurgan]] burial sites.<ref name=arch/> In the late 19th century there was some flow along the tributary before it petered out in marshlands.<ref>Russia in central Asia, translated from Der russische Feldzug nach Chiwa by J.W. Ozanne and H. Sachs https://books.google.com/books?id=p3sIAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA242&lpg=PA242&dq=kuvan+darya&source=bl&ots=EmPUu78hFP&sig=K8kAW9lWLsCrVrKTN2yuCM-R_dM&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiA6sXz_IrZAhUOca0KHfOfDSEQ6AEIUTAO#v=onepage&q=kuvan%20darya&f=false page 242</ref>

